ğŸ§  HINTS & PATTERNS (REAL-WORLD / EXAM USE)
ProcMon + x64dbg combo is killer: Always use ProcMon to find where stuffâ€™s dropped, then x64dbg to see whatâ€™s loaded into memory.

Memory dump â‰  useless blob: If you see MZ or .NETFramework in strings, youâ€™re sitting on a reverse-engineering goldmine.

Find PowerShell chains: Encoded PS in bat files is often used for lateral movement or privilege escalation.

Static + Dynamic > One or the other: Reverse the binary AND monitor its runtime â€” lots of thick client magic is runtime-dependent.

Look for RunAs logic: Hardcoded credentials are often embedded in thick clients that perform actions on behalf of users.

x64dbg settings: Turn off all breakpoints except exit â€” avoids wasting time in DLL hell during load.

